<br>
1) Can a druid do damage to mobs when he is oom? No, but a mage can (pet + BoB)<br>
<br>
2) What is the druid´s role on raids? No, it is not nuking... They are 'reduced' to group leaders and have to keep other classes alive with their pathetic heals - sorry, if i offend druis now. I don´t know if you all realize how hard it can be to keep all groupmembers alive when all you can do is casting a 1k heal (believe me when i say that you can loose 1k health real fast if you get a bad dot or are hit by rampage, hehe). Most uber mobs aggro when you are below 2 bubs of health and if the druid can´t keep your health above that the mob will eiter run to you or will summon. <br>
